### LangChain4j Demo - Test Requests

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

### ============================================
### Demo Endpoints
### ============================================

### Get Demo Info
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/demo/info

### Run All Demos (This will take a minute)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/demo/all

### ============================================
### Simple Chat Endpoints
### ============================================

### Simple Chat - Basic Question
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/simple
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "What is LangChain4j in one sentence?"
}

### Simple Chat - Technical Question
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/simple
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "Explain Java Streams API"
}

### Chat with System Message
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/system
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "systemMessage": "You are a helpful Java expert. Be concise and technical.",
  "userMessage": "What is Spring Boot?"
}

### ============================================
### AI Assistant Endpoints
### ============================================

### AI Assistant Chat
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/assistant
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "What do you know about LangChain4j?"
}

### Greet User
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/greet
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Pardhiv"
}

### Translate to Malayalam
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/translate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "text": "Hello, how are you today?",
  "language": "Malayalam"
}

### Translate to French
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/translate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "text": "Good morning, welcome to our application",
  "language": "French"
}

### Translate to German
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/translate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "text": "Thank you for using our service",
  "language": "German"
}

### ============================================
### RAG Endpoints
### ============================================

### Ingest Sample Documents - Java & Spring
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/ingest
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "documents": [
    "Pardhiv Krishna is a software engineer based in India. He is actively involved in backend development and works with Java technologies.",
    "Pardhiv is currently exploring LangChain4j to integrate Large Language Models into Java applications for building intelligent systems.",
    "He completed his graduation in B.Tech Computer Science Engineering with a specialization in Artificial Intelligence from Muthoot Institute of Technology and Science.",
    "Pardhiv is currently working at IBM on the WebSphere and Liberty projects.",
    "In his free time, Pardhiv enjoys watching movies, playing cricket, and video games."
  ]
}

### Ingest Sample Documents - TechNova
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/ingest
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "documents": [
    "TechNova Systems has developed a platform called QuantumSync Engine to optimize cloud workloads using predictive scaling.",
    "QuantumSync Engine has three main modules: SyncCore, LoadBalancerX, and PredictAI.",
    "The internal testing identifier for QuantumSync Engine is QSE-9981-X.",
    "TechNova uses a deployment validation process called GreenGate Validation to ensure zero-downtime releases.",
    "In case of failures, the emergency rollback keyword used is RED-FLAG-77."
  ]
}

### Query RAG - About Pardhiv
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": "Who is Pardhiv?"
}

### Query RAG - About Pardhiv's graduation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": "What did Pardhiv do for graduation?"
}

### Query RAG - About QuantumSync Engine
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": "What is QuantumSync Engine?"
}

### Query RAG - About QuantumSync Engine testing identifier
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": "What is the testing identifier used for QuantumSync Engine?"
}

### Get RAG Statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/stats

### ============================================
### Test Sequence for Demo
### ============================================

### 1. First, ingest some documents
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/ingest (use one of the above)

### 2. Then query without RAG to see the difference
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/simple

### 3. Finally query with RAG to see improved response
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query

### ============================================
### Error Testing
### ============================================

### Test Empty Message
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/simple
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": ""
}

### Test Missing Question
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": ""
}

### Test Empty Documents
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/ingest
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "documents": []
}